Thanks Alex.  I defined T_OBJECT to be &#39;7&#39; and committed change to HEAD.

I also committed first cut at features we discussed last week.  Now a 
call to checkpoint manages the pausing, actual checkpoint, and resume if 
crawler is in mid-flight when checkpointing is invoked  Also added 
facility that will run a timer thread that will invoke checkpointing on 
a period if a period has been set in heritrix.properties (See user 
manual for detail).  Finally, I made it so you can pass a 
CrawlJobHandler to a Heritrix constructor.  Should take care of the race 
condition you reported last week.  But to use it you&#39;ll have to make 
your own version of Heritrix.main.  If there is any refactoring of 
Heritrix.main that would make your life easier, just send over a patch.

Yours,
St.Ack

